      "content": "**Features decreasing hERG blockade likelihood**\n- **Insufficient hydrophobic/aromatic bulk**: Many potent hERG blockers have **two hydrophobic/aromatic regions** flanking a basic center (or at least substantial lipophilicity). Here there is **only one small heteroaromatic ring** and the rest is relatively polar.\n- **High polarity / likely low logD at pH 7.4**: a strongly protonated amidine-like group plus multiple heteroatoms tends to reduce membrane partitioning and may reduce effective access/affinity to the hydrophobic hERG cavity.\n- **Heteroaromatic is \u201chetero-rich\u201d**: compared with phenyl, this ring is less hydrophobic and may provide weaker \u03c0-stacking in the lipophilic pocket.",
